==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saponify
<hw>Sa*pon"i*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Saponified</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Saponifying</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>sapo</ets>, <ets>-onis</ets>, soap + <ets>-fy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>saponifier</ets>.]</ety> <def>To convert into soap, as tallow or
any fat; hence <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, to subject to any similar process, as
that which ethereal salts undergo in decomposition; <as>as, to
<ex>saponify</ex> ethyl acetate</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saponin</ent>⟦br⟧
